"...I was reading a book called Hitler’s Table Talk, which was a collection of his spontaneous utterances at mealtimes collected over about three years. It really affected my reading of it, because the number of times he used parasite metaphors really stuck in my mind."⁣
⁣
"I started to look at all of the Nazi propaganda from before the Second World War in terms of parasite-stress hypothesis, especially after I also realized that Hitler’s extermination campaign arguably had its origins in public health policy because they started out with tuberculosis interventions. Then they went to “clean up” the mental hospitals, and so on."⁣
⁣
More of this podcast (S4 E38) is available via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/10/21.

My podcast with Carl Ruck and @brian_muraresku was released on Monday. It's available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify.⁣
⁣
Click the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/14/21.

I sat down with Carl Ruck and Brian Muraresku to unravel the secrets of ancient Greek culture and religion and how psychedelics have altered the realities of Western culture.⁣
⁣
@Brian_Muraresku shares how and why he was drawn to research the role of psychedelics within Western civilization. Muraresku is also the author of "The Immortality Key: The Secret History of the Religion With No Name".⁣
⁣
Carl Ruck is an American professor who’s known for his work and extensive research on mythology and religion regarding the sacred role of entheogens; a selection of psychoactive plants that are known for inducing altered states of reality or consciousness.⁣
⁣
This episode was recorded on May 14th, 2021.⁣
⁣
The entire conversation is now available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify. Click the link in my bio to watch or listen.

⁣
The episode was recorded on May 7th.

"...I was reading a book called Hitler’s Table Talk, which was a collection of his spontaneous utterances at mealtimes collected over about three years. It really affected my reading of it, because the number of times he used parasite metaphors really stuck in my mind."⁣
⁣
"I started to look at all of the Nazi propaganda from before the Second World War in terms of parasite-stress hypothesis, especially after I also realized that Hitler’s extermination campaign arguably had its origins in public health policy because they started out with tuberculosis interventions. Then they went to “clean up” the mental hospitals, and so on."⁣
⁣
More of this podcast (S4 E38) is available via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/10/21.

The Irony of North Korea.⁣
⁣
@Yeonmi_Park points out that the irony of North Korea is that it was founded on the idea of equality; A socialist paradise. In fact, they divided the population into 3 categories and then a further 50 subcategories of the original 3. She explains that the consequence was that it made North Korea an incredibly unequal society.⁣

Watch the full podcast on my YouTube channel.
⁣

⁣

Watch or listen to it via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/10/21.
